[[File:Ant-pen-map-Oscar-II.PNG|thumb|Location of Oscar II Coast on Antarctic Peninsula.]]
'''Zahariev Peak''' ({{lang-bg|''<U+0417><U+0430><U+0445><U+0430><U+0440><U+0438><U+0435><U+0432> <U+0432><U+0440><U+044A><U+0445>''}}, <U+2018>Zahariev Vrah<U+2019> \za-'ha-ri-ev 'vr&h\) is the rocky, partly ice-free peak rising to 650 m in [[Metlichina Ridge]] on [[Oscar II Coast]], [[Graham Land]] in [[Antarctica]].  It is overlooking [[Punchbowl Glacier]] to the northeast and [[Borima Bay]] to the southwest.

The feature is named after the [[Bulgarians|Bulgarian]] [[meteorology|meteorologist]] Vasil Zahariev (1929-2006) who worked at the [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] base [[Mirny Station|Mirny]] in 1967-69.

==Location==

Zahariev Peak is located at {{coord|65|10|42|S|62|03|19|W|display=inline, title}}, which is 3.9 km south of [[St. Angelariy Peak]], 2.58 km northwest of [[Chapanov Peak]] and 5.45 km east-northeast of [[Yordanov Nunatak]].  [[United Kingdom|British]] mapping in 1974.

